🔗 SECTION 5: FEATURE CONNECTION MAP
Modifying one system impacts others. Always trace the full chain before making changes.
Job Posting (Customer)

Trigger: LocationScheduleScreen → POST /api/jobs
Writes to MySQL jobs table → triggers matchingEngine.js → spawns active_jobs Firebase node → fires Job Alert FCM to nearby workers

Wave Matching (Backend)

Trigger: Job Posting → reads worker_profiles
Modifies job_worker_notifications → fires FCM to subsequent worker waves based on timeouts in jobs.config.json

Job Acceptance (Backend)

Trigger: Worker accepts via mobile FCM prompt
Redis NX lock protects from race conditions → MySQL overrides status=assigned → Firebase synchronized → Customer receives FCM

Start / End OTP Verification

Trigger: Mobile inputs code
Server performs bcrypt.compare → on failure (5×): Auto-Dispute → on success: transitions Job State, generates Invoice

Invoicing

Trigger: Successful End OTP
Data read strictly from server DB and jobs.config.json rates → Payout split calculated securely on server → MySQL → Firebase → FCM (Trifecta)


🏗️ SECTION 6: SCHEMA CHANGE PROTOCOL
Never mutate tables manually. All schema changes must follow this pipeline exactly:

Create the ALTER TABLE script logic
Alter the database
Update the Backend Service querying that table
Update the API Route formatting object
Update the Mobile feature store and types mapped to that object

Safety check: If dropping a column, audit every SELECT * and specific SELECT query that references that column before executing.

